In addition to regulating the migration of non-specific leukocytes during inflammatory responses, CCR5 controls the action of specific cell types, including natural killer (NK) cells (
 Khan et al., 2006; 
 Weiss et al., 2011) and regulatory T (Treg) cells (
 Wysocki et al., 2005; 
 Tan et al., 2009; 
 Dobaczewski et al., 2010). CCR5 is also expressed by tissue-resident memory T cells. These CCR5
 + cells support barrier immunity (
 Davis et al., 2019).
